But we did find this little treasure
Vodafone Prepaid
In 1996, Vodafone introduced the UK's first prepaid phone service. Before this, mobile phone services were all contract-based, which meant paying upfront (excluding many from owning a mobile).
Following this up in October 1997, Vodafone UK launched 'Pay as you Talk,' packaging a GSM phone with a prepay tariff making mobiles affordable for all.
